<p>I have a slider made with css only. I tried to add the pagination with radio inputs but it doesn't seem to work. Here is the html markup:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="slider-wrap"&gt;   &lt;input type="checkbox" id="1"&gt;   &lt;label for="1"&gt;&lt;/label&gt;   &lt;input type="checkbox" id="2"&gt;   &lt;label for="2"&gt;&lt;/label&gt;   &lt;input type="checkbox" id="3"&gt;   &lt;label for="3"&gt;&lt;/label&gt; &lt;ul class="slider"&gt;   &lt;li class="slide"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li class="slide"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li class="slide"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li class="slide"&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; </code></pre>  <p> This is the css:</p>  <pre><code>body,html{   margin:0;   padding:0;   width:100%;   height:100%; } ul.slider{   list-style:none;   width:100%;   height:100%; } .slide{   width:100%;   height:100%;   position:absolute;   top:0;   left:0;   display:block;   opacity:0;   animation:imageAnimation 24s linear infinite; } .slide:first-child{   background-color:red; } .slide:nth-child(2){   background-color:blue;   animation-delay:6s; } .slide:nth-child(3){   background-color:pink;   animation-delay:12s; } .slide:last-child{   background-color:green;   animation-delay:18s; } @keyframes imageAnimation {      0% {         opacity:0;     }     6% {         opacity:1;     }     24% {         opacity:1;     }     30% {         opacity:0;     }     100% {         opacity:0;     } }  input[type=checkbox]{   display:none; } label{   width:12px;   height:12px;   dislay:block;   position:absolute;   border-radius:50%;   border:1px solid black;   left:4px;   top:3px;   z-index:999; } label:nth-of-type(2){   left:30px; } label:nth-of-type(3){   left:56px; } </code></pre>  <p>Here is a working example:<a href="http://codepen.io/M1k1dut/pen/QjdYNN" rel="nofollow">http://codepen.io/M1k1dut/pen/QjdYNN</a>. Thanks.</p>